         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>It is anticipated that the procurement will commence early in May 2018, with appointments to a Framework being made in December 2018. It is envisaged that individual work packages will vary in value up to a maximum value of 20 000 000 GBP and will be procured via mini-competitions over a 4-year period.</P>
               <P>It is anticipated that the Form of Contract for the Framework Agreement will be the Council’s standard terms and conditions and the Call-off terms that will apply to each order placed under the Framework Agreement will be NEC3 Engineering and Construction Contract (as amended by the Local Authority).</P>
               <P>The purpose of this notice is to raise awareness of this forthcoming opportunity and seek return of a market engagement questionnaire.</P>
               <P>The market engagement questionnaire is available within the attachments section of this notice.</P>
               <P>Please arrange for the Market Engagement Questionnaire to be completed in word format, and forwarded by email to:-.</P>
               <P>Demi.Milne@ced.glasgow.gov.uk</P>
               <P>Deadline for return of completed forms is close of Business on Wednesday 21.3.2018.</P>
               <P>NOTE: To register your interest in this notice and obtain any additional information please visit the Public Contracts Scotland Web Site at http://www.publiccontractsscotland.gov.uk/Search/Search_Switch.aspx?ID=530488</P>
               <P>(SC Ref:530488).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
